        {
          "id": "b3a424787e4b_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1406",
          "text": "For more information on ecological footprinting and comparisons of different ecological footprints by country please take a closer look at the website of the Footprint Network. Some countries exceed their biocapacity constraints. That means they are borrowing resources from future generations within their own country and also importing such borrowed resources from other countries.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 150,
              "href": "http://www.footprintnetwork.org/en/index.php/GFN/page/footprint_basics_overview/",
              "rel": "noopener",
              "start": 143,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 216,
              "href": "http://www.footprintnetwork.org/en/index.php/GFN/page/glossary/#biocapacity",
              "rel": "noopener",
              "start": 205,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "b3a424787e4b_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "aefc",
          "text": "There are very few countries in the world that live within their biocapacity, and these are primarily those countries with vast open spaces with substantial biomass, such as, Canada and Brazil (see map below). On a planetary scale humanity has gone into overshoot in the late 1960s. Overshoot in this context means that we started living of the capital rather than the interest of what the bioproductivity of the planet provide to regeneration each year.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "b3a424787e4b_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b7da",
          "text": "Source",
